Forms & Input Elements

File Name: form.html

Task Description:
Create a registration form using HTML with proper labels and appropriate input types. 
Style the form using CSS to make it visually appealing and professional.

Form Fields Included:

1. Full Name
- Input type: text
- Used for entering user's name

2. Email
- Input type: email
- Validates correct email format

3. Phone Number
- Input type: tel
- Accepts numeric phone input

4. Password
- Input type: password
- Hides entered characters for security

5. Gender
- Input type: radio buttons
- Allows user to select one option (Male, Female, Other)

6. Submit Button
- Styled button with hover effect
- Used to submit the form

Design Features:

- Purple gradient background
- Centered registration card
- Rounded corners and shadow effects
- Input focus highlight effect
- Clean spacing and alignment
- Smooth fade-in animation

Expected Outcome:
The registration form should collect user details using appropriate input types and display a professional UI design.

Actual Outcome:
The form successfully displays all required input fields with proper labels, validation, and styled layout.

Learning Outcome:
- Learned different HTML input types
- Understood the importance of label tags
- Implemented radio button grouping
- Applied CSS styling to forms
- Improved UI design skills
